@joewitt @trixpan I think the provenance linkage should already be happening automatically with the following line:

`FlowFile split = session.create(originalFlowFile);`

With that call, the framework will create a fork event from the parent for each attachment.

A bit nit picky and I may be alone here, but I find putting "if" statements and their content on the same line a bit hard to read when trying to read someone else's code. For example line 107 of GetAWSIoT[1]. When reviewing it's nice to distinctly see "if" statements condition and content. 

I would prefer the bit more verbose but easier consume longer format (with tab/space before the content, github auto-trims):
if (awsQos == 0) {
    mqttClient.unsubscribe(awsTopic);
}

